Package abstractDataType

Interface GenericListADTNode<T>

All Known Implementing Classes:
GenericElementNode, GenericEmptyNode
public interface GenericListADTNode<T>
This generic interface represents all the operations to be supported by a list of objects of type T

      GenericListADTNode<T> add(int index, T b) throws IllegalArgumentException
      A method that adds the given object at the given index in this list . If index is 0, it means this object should be added to the front of this list
      Parameters:

    • map

      <R> GenericListADTNode<R> map(Function<T,R> converter)
      A general map higher order function on nodes. This returns a list of identical structure, but each data item of type T converted into R using the provided converter method.
      Type Parameters:
      R - the type of the data in the returned list
      Parameters:
      converter - the function needed to convert T into R
      Returns:
      the head of a list that is structurally identical to this list, but contains data of type R
